                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2681">John the scholastic</persName> wrote a letter to 
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/51">Severus</persName> 
                            in which he sought answers to questions someone else had asked him. The questions dealt with repentance for
                            refusing to submit to monastic discipline and repentance for self-castration in one's youth.
                            <listRelation>
                                <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/sender-of-letter-to" active="http://syriaca.org/person/51" passive="http://syriaca.org/person/2681"/>
